reviews:
We (2 adults and children) had a wonderful stay and will definitely come back.
The hotel is stylish decorated with a good atmosphere and a small garden.
The staff was very friendly, helpful and welcoming.
The location is beautiful and perfect for enjoying Paris, having an evening drink/dinner in busy Montmartre and still come "home" to a quiet and peaceful street, where it's possible to sleep with the windows open without getting disturbed by any outside noise.
We stayed in an apartment, two rooms and kitchenette.

This is a very clean and comfortable hotel. We enjoyed staying here and would definitely recommend it.

Our room was of good size and very comfortable. It overlooked the front, but there was no noise as the windows and walls are well insulated. The bathroom was small and the bathtub was narrow, although it had a powerful shower head above.

On the ground floor next to the reception area is a smart dining area. We only had coffee here and relaxed in the comfortable sofas.

The staff are very friendly and gave us sightseeing tips and advice in fluent English.

We loved the location - it’s in a quieter, semi-residential district, whilst still close to several shops, cafes, restaurants and bars. Most importantly it’s around the corner from the stunning Sacre Coeur and the artists’ square.

We like walking and enjoyed ‘getting the steps in’ by strolling down the hill to the central areas and main sights. The funicular makes this hill climb easier for those wishing to take this option.

The bus is a great option for getting to and from the hotel. We used it to return to the hotel on one occasion - the hotel is located close to two stops - tickets are cheap.

The overall stay was fantastic, the staff was very kind although the cleaning ladies didn't speak English very well in my opinion. The room was clean, spacious enough, and is provided with a microwave, dish washer and some utensils; the dish washer doesn't clean much in my opinion. The location is hard-ish to reach, with seriously a lot of stairs of uphills (there are metro nearby but still a lot of stairs).

We arrived a little later than expected but we’re welcomed by a lovely friendly lady on reception .
We were a little tired from walking from Gare du Nord and up stairs. She offered us water to refresh.
Our room was on the 3rd floor ,plenty of lifts .First impression the room was smaller than expected,however after staying 3nights it was perfect . We moved the desk next to the window and spent evenings and mornings gazing at the Sacre Coeur .Apartment fully equipped with everything you need ,we loved making coffee from the filter machine (take filter papers though ) the bathroom with bath and shower was welcomed after 50mile walks to relax the bath perfect for lying in! We didn’t have breakfast in the hotel as we prepared this ourselves again sat gazing from apartment windows, peaceful location .Staff were always friendly and offered help with locations or recommendations.
The apartments although located up stairs/hill behind Sacre Couer were a perfect location for exploring the whole of Paris and I can assure you we did ! If you leave apartment turn left to the middle St Vincent’s and go down steps the Brasserie on your left is amazing and reasonable.Although you’re never be without a bistro or bar all close by. Plenty of Happy Hours.
The beds as mentioned in other reviews are a little hard but we both slept well, just a little warm at night but we open the window as so quite.
Overall we are fussy but we will definitely return here . Thank you Odalys.

Overall very good. The décor is a bit spare and the furniture int he room is basic but serviceable - more like a business hotel. The main downside is the room make up policy. If you stay 5 days or more they only make up the room once a week! After 4 days we had to ask for fresh towels, and we only got tea and coffee on the first day. Not exactly 4 Star service. The staff were friendly and accommodating. The best thing is the location just behind Sacre Coeur on a quiet street - just a few steps from the centre of Montmartre and a short walk to several Metro stations..

Warm and friendly staff, modern comfortable clean rooms, amazing location at the top of Montmartre and surprisingly quiet in the room. Would definitely stay again but would bring my own pillows as this was the only down side to this lovely hotel. Can’t wait to return!

Located right behind the Sacre Coure. If you are desperate to be based right at the top of the hill in Montmartre this place would be perfect. We actually found the hotel very frustrating as they deactivated both the aircon units and the radiators in the room which meant we couldn’t control the temp in the room ourselves. Our room was crazy hot at night with the 4 of us in there which meant we had to open the windows which meant the noise from the street outside flooded into our room which meant we all got very little sleep across our 3 night stay. I’d also add the beds were hard and the pillows barely had any filling in them so your head was basically lying flat on the mattress. They also charged €25 a night for parking, €15 a night for our dog and €18 per person to use the hotel hot tub which I thought was a bit annoying given we spent €420 a night for our stay.

To put my review in context, please bear in mind that I have travelled to Paris many many times, so I don't have any hurry to get to places or sightseeing and can spend 45 to 60 minutes going anywhere.

I was a little sceptical before staying at this place as I had never heard of this chain, but I have to admit that I was pleasantly surprised. The property is very clean and bright, rooms are spacious for Paris standards, and they have a small kitchenette. Overall, I think it is great value for money.

The hotel is located next to the Monmartre church and about 7 minutes walk to the nearest metro station. This means that if you have a large suitcase and are not willing to pay taxis to get from and to the airport, most likely this is not a good option since you will have to drag your bags uphills and through cobblestone streets. Just my advice.

The Hotel is fantastic, amazing views. Clean and well organised. Rooms are spacious and have all the facilities you may need: even a dishwasher in the room! Breakfast was high quality and buffet style so you could eat as much as you wanted.
The staff were outstanding and were happy to help with any request.

We've enjoyed our stay in the Odalys App. Hotel (Paris Montmartre). The staff was very kind and friendly. Definitely a recommendation. It is nearby Montmartre where the Sacre Coeur is located. The room was clean and relaxing.

ES
La verdad tuvimos una muy mala experiencia en el hotel. Nos dieron 2 camas pegadas para nosotros 2, que somos una pareja. Los 4 días que estuvimos les pedimos que nos den UNA cama, no 2 pegadas. No lo resolvieron, en su lugar nos dieron desayuno, cuando solamente queríamos dormir bien para seguir disfrutando París al día siguiente. Colchón duro, incómodo, almohadas con poco relleno. La primera noche sonó la alarma de incendio del hotel y tuvimos que salir todos los huéspedes en pijama, fue una falsa alarma. No nos reembolsaron nada del dinero invertido en un hotel 4 estrellas cuando nuestro descanso fue pésimo. La habitación standard muy pequeña. No lo recomiendo.

EN
We really had a very bad experience at the hotel. They gave us 2 beds pushed together for the 2 of us who are a couple. The 4 days we stayed, we asked them to give us ONE bed, not 2 pushed together. They did not solve it, instead they gave us breakfast, when we only wanted to sleep well to continue enjoying Paris the next day. Hard mattress, uncomfortable, pillows with little padding. The first night the hotel fire alarm went off and all the guests had to leave in their pajamas, it was a false alarm. They did not refund any of the money invested in a 4-star hotel when our rest was lousy. The standard room is very small. I do not recommend it

Wonderful place. Fantastic top class service- friendly yet non obsequious help from the front desk, eg taxi ordering and minding bags on our last day. (15 euros to G de N). Quiet, clean room on ground floor at back. Supply dw tablets wash liquid. Fridge. Glasses,dishes . There is a filter paper coffee machine . Great comfy super size bed! Quiet location behind S Coeur , nice to hear the bells ring (only during the day). Excellent location to wander Montmartre. Be prepared for the many steps. Near restaurants etc- stay away from over priced Place de Tertre

The breakfast is delicious, the staff is incredibly kind and helpful and the beds are extremely comfortable. The view from the room over the city is beautiful and the hotel is located in a neighborhood with great vibes at night.

Location is superb right smack at the back of Sacre Coeur in Montmartre. Just a short walk to several tourist spots along the area and restaurants and cafes. Since it is Montmartre, there are lots of stairs to tackle to go places. Our room is nice, clean and spacious. Although it has a kitchenette, it’s not a good idea to cook as there is no exhaust to absorb steam from cooking. Beds and pillows are comfortable to sleep in.

The Odalys Montmartre apartments are perfectly situated for the exploration on foot of the very beautiful and interesting area of Montmartre. It is also very convenient for public transport for further exploration of Paris. The staff were very friendly and helpful. The entrance and reception to the building is bright, spacious and very well kept. The room we stayed in was very clean, modern and of a good size for our needs, perfect for Paris city tourists and great value. We highly recommend and will definitely use again when we can Odalys in Paris

I booked an apartment over three months in advance. The morning of our arrival date, when we were already en voyage, I received a message saying they were 'overbooked' and were cancelling my reservation. Booking.com suggested an alternative for the same price which was an inferior room in a less attractive district; in the circumstances I was obliged to accept this. The way we were treated was absolutely disgusting. Avoid this place at sasll costs.

We ended up at Hotel Odalys quite by accident. Due to a schedule issue, we ended up getting to stay in Paris for an extra day and knight. Unable to add another night to our lodging near Les Halles, we found Odalys on Booking.com and could not have been happier. The property is modern, comfortable and quiet with a helpful and friendly staff. The location was perfect for us. It is a block north of Sacre Coeur so just around the corner from Place du Tertre but away from the noise and down the hill to the north is a much quieter neighborhood full of restaurants and shops. If we get the chance to go back to Paris, I would love to stay at Hotel Odalys again.

Would definitely recommend - great size room with very comfortable bed, spotless bathroom and lovely views (4th floor). Kitchenette looked very well equipped. Good storage provided. Staff really friendly and helpful - happy to store luggage, arranged a taxi. I was travelling alone, and I felt they went out of their way to make sure I was alright.

Do not part with your money here. Unfortunately we had to cancel on day of departure as my passport was stuck in Indian embassy. I cancelled and was told I would get 1 nights stay back. Weeks later and 2 emails no response and no refund. I called shortly after to say maybe we could move it the poor girl on the phone was shouted at and bullied by her colleagues whilst I listened.

I will never stay here on principle and as a travel agent never recommend.

Please be warned

I Booked my stay in October for January 2023 but unfortunately had to cancel my booking. Even with 4 months ahead they charged me the full amount. Extremely bad service. There was no understanding or whatsoever. Be careful with these guys..

Beautiful, clean, the breakfast buffet was exceptional, and the staff was perfect; friendly and oh so helpful.

The location in Montmartre, just behind Sacre Coeur, was quiet and secluded.

Exceeded all our expectations, and we have recommended the hotel to anyone traveling to Paris.

This hotel is in an amazing location right behind the Basilica. It was clean and modern and the staff were very good. Despite my attempts to speak French they spoke great English.

The room was very functional without many frills. There is a little kitchenette that we only really used the fridge to chill wine. There were wine glasses and a bottle opener in the cupboard. It's great as a base to explore Montmartre.

The bed wasn't the comfiest but we slept well. The bed was a bit noisy - something to bear in mind if you're on a romantic city break ;)

We didn't try out the spa facilities or the breakfast.

Fantastic location in possibly the best area to stay in Paris. Rooms were more than adequate and the staff were friendly. We didn’t have breakfast but the buffet looked like it was good quality. I would stay again

Everything is better than you see on pictures. Definitely coming back to same place when opportunity occurs. Very clean and tidy. Polite and helpful staff. Quiet place and neighborhood. Perfect choice!

A mealy nice hotel in a super location just behind Sacré Coeur. Spacious room, air conditioner, nice breakfast, helpful staff. The hike up the hill from the Château Rouge métro station was a challenge, but worth it.

I like my stay at the hotel . However, there were some problems with kitchen layout. Large cabinet door was covering the fridge, so to open it, I have to open two doors, then close both of them. That was just inconvenient. The bigger problem was the same large door over the stove. When opened it obstructed the passage. I struck my head on that door really hard, had to use ice and treat the wound with antibiotic. Another issue is very slippery bath tub.

Lovely place, good quality hotel room and service with exceptional staff who were professional and very friendly. I was particularly impressed by Christian at Reception who showed much initiative, but everyone was so helpful and just pleasant to deal with.

Very disappointing stay at this hotel. Initial impressions were very good with great reception staff and large well appointed room.

Sadly things quickly unravelled…

Firstly the air con started to leak overnight onto my daughter who was sleeping below. As such she had to sleep with aircon off on one of the hottest nights on record. On reporting this next day we were told to only set aircon 10 degrees maximum below ambient air temp. If this is the case we should have been told at check in. Despite then following the instructions it continued to leak the next night again waking may daughter and having to turn it off.

Secondly the overflow in the kitchen sink wasn’t connected (Room 101). This is a very small sink as such with dishes in likely to have to use the overflow. As such water leaked all over the floor.

Thirdly there was only enough crockery/cutlery sets for 3 people which wasn’t helpful as the room was a family room for 4. As such only 3 of us could eat at one time.

Fourthly the internet was absolutely dreadful. I couldn’t even access emails and had to spent the whole time using 4G at my personal cost. Not what you expect from staying in a modern hotel.

Finally the fire alarm went off at 9pm one evening. We had no instructions from staff on what was going on and eventually when alarm went off we just went back to the room. We still have no idea what happened or if it was safe to go back in but we gave up waiting. No apology we given at all.

Over all as you can see from the above a lot of areas need addressing. For over €300 per night (excluding breakfast) there are better options.

Finally I planned to email the company explaining the issues. To make a complaint you have to write a letter and can’t send an email…. Very poor.

Everything was great, the location, breakfast and the stuff. The view from the window was wonderful, being able to see Sacre Coeur.
The stuff from the reception was very friendly and eager to help.
We highly recommend this hotel if you want to visit Paris.

5 days stay, no cleaning, no toilet paper or towels, no garbage collection. I bag for one week daily after check out to unblock the guarantee fee. Almost every time told me lies. I ask many times for cleaning. The answer from front desk was "the cleaning lady is tired..."

Very modern and clean hotel. Staff always helpful and friendly. Amazing atmosphere at artists square and views from near by bazilic.
The only dawn side: to many steps to get to, but it is worth the effort.

Very good stay with the family in a lovely modern and clean place. Friendly and helpful reception staff. Nicely spacious apartment with bedroom, sofa bed in a separate room, two tvs, a tablet to use, a safe, and a kitchenette with plenty of equipment. Separate bath and toilet rooms. Did not have the breakfast there but it smelled good. Just around the corner from the atmosphere of Montmartre and a five minute walk to Lamarck Metro station, which handily has a lift. Bit intimidated by a sign over the sink in our room, to wash and put away the dishes after each use, or we would be charged for the service. I’d prefer if it said guests, not the cleaners, were responsible for washing the dishes, then we could do it any time in our stay that we felt like it. But…minor niggle. Would definitely stay there again.

The perfect place, on the perfect location for a visit in Paris, we definitaly will come back!
Great service very quit you don't notice that you are in a big city near by the great tourist areas. Very jind personel, the room was perfect, everythi g we needed was on the room, great beds!

Super break in Odalys. Staff are so friendly and helpful. Rooms are very clean, warm and comfortable. We could see the bell tower of the Sacre Coeur from our room. Lovely quiet street. Nice area with lots of little cafes and restaurants.

I booked a stay for my family with booking.com. Less than 24 hours before our departure to Paris, I received a notification from the hotel that my booking was cancelled.

When calling the hotel shortly after, I was told that nothing could be done since the hotel was fully booked on our dates.

When complaining about this issue to the hotel, I was given the excuse that the cancellation was due to an invalid credit card number, despite the fact that I could see a successful credit card validation in my card statement.

I would therefore like to warn other travelers about unexpected cancellations such as ours.

The location of Odalys is amazing and the staff are very friendly. We loved the shutters on the outside of the window to make the room very dark. We asked for a quiet room, whilst it did not have any noise from the outside, there was a lot of white noise in the room e.g. whirring of fans or machinery. I also found the bed not very comfortable (relatively thin foam mattress and very firm pillows). We also found the room too hot and dry, and the air con was disabled for winter (fair enough from an environmental perspective but room was still too hot with heating off and windows open). Overall I would not stay here again but I would still recommend to others with these caveats.

Loved the location. Nice staff. Nice room and clean. Very comfortable.
I would come again . Thanks for a Nice stay . There is an elevator Which we didnt expect because of pre reviews…and safe area……..

Me and my partner were due to travel to Paris December 2021. However, just before we travelled France changed their COVID rules and banned all UK tourists from entering. The hotel refused to change the dates of our booking, offer a voucher or even give a part refund. Very disappointed by the customer service. I would understand if we were asking for a full refund or if it was due to a fault of our own that we couldn't travel but we legally could not enter the country. Very disappointed.

We went with my partner. I recommand this hotel who has very nice room of good size, which is very well located and offers reasonable proce for the quality. I will come back there for my next trip to Paris.

Very clean and as demonstrated on pictures and web site. Walking distance to the cathedral and multiple small fun restaurants. I would recommend if you want a quiet place to stay with huge rooms in Paris.

excellent services, pleasant and quiet environment, Nice attractive location, but on a hill,
Zavazadla si musíte nechat dovézt taxíkem, autobus jezdí jen dvakrát za hodinu, metro je kousek z kopce dolů nebo lze využít pozemní lanovku

Perfect location in the quieter area of Montmartre. Clean and spacious rooms and helpful and friendly staff. Short walk to a vibrant area with lots of bars and restaurants. Very close to Sacre Coeur and great views over Paris. Close to metro line which makes it easy to explore Paris. The hotel is located in a nice quiet location which feels more like a small village than part of a large city. Highly recommend. staying here.

Really nice experience the location is close to everything the room small but comfortable nice view from the room the spa is nice and you can enjoy privately really nice place to stay for sure i will come back

Perfect location, wonderful staff, quiet, very clean and everything works. Will definitely book our next Paris stay at Odalys. Loved climbing those steps and being so centrally located in such a beautiful city.

A lovely, clean hotel with excellent-sized rooms. Room was humid in Paris summer, but the excellent reception staff provided us with a fan. Staff were all friendly. Bed was very comfortable. Lovely place

Stayed for 1 night and been the worst hotel I’ve ever been in my life. No air cond and instead they gave you 2 small fans which makes a horrible noise. In London this hotel will have 2** not 4. AVOID.

We had a nice room with a good view on the city. A separate bedroom and a living room, we were able to sleep with four persons (two adults and two children) in a comfortable way.
There was even a kitchen and two televisions in the room, a real family room which is usable to stay for a few days.

Always great here, I stayed many times. Make sure you install Op & Go to pay for parking because machine in street is very far. This hotel is perfectly situated. Try restaurant le Potager, doesn' t look fancy but the food is great

When one cannot get a room in the Eiffel tower (too touristy), the Appart'hotel Odlays in Monmatre is the second best. Just behind the Sacre Coeur with an entire view of Paris two minutes away from the hotel. Included in the price is good training up and down the streets and stairways of the Montmartre. The Montmartre is so quiet in the evening and the hotel is outside the most crowded parts of the summit. We had a great stay!

The room was very clean and large for Paris. I love the Sacre Coeur area! we wanted to have a small kitchen for having a big fridge (drinks!), hot water cooker for tea and knives&plates for eating baguette and cheese at random hours. Since we stay up very late (one time we had a nocturne at the Louvre and returned at the hotel at 3 am) we were very happy we were not wakened by housekeeping. Even when we only left the room at 12, it stil was cleaned when we returned at night.

I'd never been to Paris before so booking a hotel in a nice area was a bit hit and miss. I'm so pleased to have stumbled on this one though which is right next to the Sacre Coeur. I stayed 3 nights and found the place perfect. Reasonably priced for Paris and spotlessly clean. The reception staff were pleasant and professional and the metro was about 400 meters away albeit up hill. I didn't try breakfast at the hotel so can't comment on that but we would definitely stay again.

Great location right next to Sacré Cœur. Room was a good size, well decorated with a great view. Had breakfast one morning but not much suitable for vegans. Staff very friendly. The health spa was lovely but expensive for just an hour.
Be aware that the area around the hotel is very hilly with lots of steep steps so not ideal for people with disabilities.
Overall though, we would definitely come here again.

We were 2 couples a staying at Odalys for 3 nights . Positives :
Excellent location just behind Sacre coeur Cathedral which is one of the highest points in Paris . Timing was prefect as our stay coincided with Montmarte wine festival which was amazing and fun filled event over 3-4 days
Lot of cafés to explore within the walking distance of the hotel which gives a great vibe to the hotel
Metro station can be easily accessed within 5 mts of walking distance down the road
Rooms were spacious with fully equipped stoves and necessary equipment to prepare quick meal. ( studio apartments )
Areas of Pigalle can be easily accessed from Montmarte

Only drawback is getting the uber during evenings as the entry points get blocked and it’s a wait unless one walks down to main road

We stayed four nights at this apartment-hotel which is located just below the Basilica of Sacre Couer in Montmartre. The accommodation clean and comfortable, is far away enough from the noise and bustle of the city and only a 15-minute walk downhill to metro stops, shops etc. There are restaurants close to the Basilica but go further (downhill) if you want something of better quality. The location was a problem for Uber drivers. On one morning we had five drivers agree to come up the hill but then bow out to be replaced by the next one. For them the trip up the hill and the one way street would have put them off if they got a fare closer on the flat. The hotel served breakfast but we did not indulge as we were saving ourselves for pastries and other goodies in town. You could also order other food that would be delivered from an outside provider. The room was of a reasonable size - a cross between a hotel room and an apartment but without some amenities you might expect from an apartment - and no milk for tea. We liked the decor and staff were obliging.

We stayed at this ApartHotel for 4 nights in October as a base for a family trip to see Paris, and could not fault it at all. The staff all spoke English and were friendly and helpful at all times. The room was excellent and it was great to have the extra bedroom to save all four of us sleeping in a confined space. Also, we liked that the "sofabed" was actually 2 separate single trundle beds, which allowed our 2 teenagers a bit more space than having to share a bed together.
It was also great to have the kitchen available as it meant we could get up later and make our own breakfast, getting fresh croissants from the nearby Boulangeries, and also had a fridge to keep our own milk, wine, soft drinks etc.
The location is great with many nearby restaurants, although watch out for a few that entice you in with a great value set menu and then sting you for drinks (€9 for a coke!).
It's only a few mins to the nearest Metro line that connects easily to the centre of Paris, although the walk back is up a fairly steep cobbled hill, so not great if you are not fully fit.
Overall, I would totally recommend this as a great value stay in Paris

We had a splendid stay here. The location was superb and very easy to get ubers into Paris centre, or walkto some lovely local cafes'. The area has charm and is not overly busy. The hotel itself was perfect! The beds were super comfortable and extremely quiet. It was also nice to be able to open the window and have fresh air instead of air con for a change. The rooms were very tidy and cleaned each day. The staff were friendly and very helpful and competent. I would not hesitate to stay here again.

Hubby arranged a birthday treat ...and what a lovely place . The room was very spacious, the staff were always friendly.
The Location was incredible 2 mins walk to the Sacre Coeur and 4 mins to Montmartre Village a great place for the evening.

Would definitely return

Located in a very quiet street, at the back of the Sacro Couer. Not the most easy location to get to, but the environment makes it one of the best spots in Paris. On top of the Montremarte you have a great view over Paris. My room was on the backside of the hotel. I could sleep with my windows open, without hearing anything. This helped a lot, because the room didn't't had airconditioning.
The rooms are spacious, modern, clean and very functional. Staff is very friendly. Breakfast was an additional 15 Euro offering a limited but nice selection of food.
The best way to get to the hotel is with the funiculaire towards the Scare Couer.
I have stayed in very expensive hotels in PAris (Hilton, Hyatt etc), but next time in Paris I will choose this hotel again.

the location of the hotel is good for visiting montmarte and parking on site is available
but no air condition in the room and it was very hot, seriously??
and i must to open the door and beaten by mosquitoes at night
i cant understand why its so difficult to put aircon
the summer in pairs is not cold one
the room size is just OK
poor breakfast

Location - ideal. Basically you're next door to the Sacre Coeur.

Room - spacious, clean, with a fridge and ... a hob if you want to get busy with a saucepan. In Paris.

Staff - helpful, approachable, professional.

Negatives - no aircon. Fine in the off season I imagine, but a bit sweaty in June.

All in all - this hotel is ridiculously good value for money.

Clean rooms, very silent at night, calm neighborhood although very close to sacré cœur. We went to a bakery nearby for breakfast and took a nespresso in the lobby. Small kitchenette. Friendly staff. Privât parking garage with large parking places for 25 euro per day

Overall we enjoyed our stay at the Odalys. The hotel room was spacious however the cleanliness level was not great. As soon as we arrived our room seemed to be covered in dust and crumbs as though it hadnt been cleaned, carpet would have been much better. The hotel was located just behind the Sacre Coeur which was excellent, however the nearest tube station was not that close, its probabaly a 10 min walk through the Sacre Coeur to Montmatre so it wasnt in the heart of the town but still a quiet and nice location. The staff was very friendly and allowed us to store our bags until we were able to check in. Great facilities and nice hotel.

Great location, but not up to 4 stars hotel. Breakfast was really poor. Just scrambled eggs, ham was not eatable. Stuff betwen eating breakfast is very annoying and all the time asking and eating and walking arround. Do not let you have peace between eating. Open shower, had to be careful water can come into room. Otherwise ok place and great location on Montmartre. If you like to walk, it is ok.

Located 150m behind the SacreCoeur church, at approx 5min from museum of Montmartre ... in a 1930s building completely refurbished. Latest décoration, brand new accommodation with 20m2 appartments equipped with wifi TV kitchenette including fridge and dish washing machine...Nice breakfast compared To usual practice in that part of Paris... taken in a veranda with view behind the hotel (garden).Very calm.Next To rue Caulaincourt for your Food wine grocery shopping as Well as restaurants and bistrots ...lovely place to walk around :-)Located next to métro lines 4 and 12 with access to many places in Paris.One caution : you may care for a good pair of shoes (uphill, paved streets)

Some folks have written not the best reviews and I am not sure of their expectations but, we were treated splendidly! Accommodations were as advertised and even better ! We will return! Liked that the had laundry on bottom floor( for fee)

Spacious room, well equipped and functional. Very clean and everything is brand new. Couldn't hear any sound inside or outside of the hotel, since location is very quiet. Above expectations for Paris prices and room standards! I would definitely recommend it.

Everything was perfect. I will certainly stay again in this hotel.The rooms are well equipped and spotless. It is located in a very calm and peaceful part of Montmartre, yet very close to the Basilique.

Excellent located hotel for Montmartre, a bit complicated to reach by car. The hotel has a private car park at €25/day. Well equipped room but horrible irritating perfume used for cleaning. Very dominating smell, irritating eyes and throat. After complaining, reception offered another room but this was no improvement: same offending smell. Management may think to please their clients by using this perfume but the opposite is true: it is a good reason for not staying here!

PROS:
- New/modern hotel
- We asked to stay on the 4th floor and we had beautiful views! Both long windows open fully.
- There is a laundry machine on floor 1.
- Very close walk to Sacré-Cœur and many cafes & gift shops around
- Safe neighborhood
- Close to Metro

CONS:
- We stayed for 8 days and the front desk told us we could only choose one day for the staff to clean our room. This is disgusting! !!!!! We paid thousands of dollars to stay this entire long week and the cleaning staff only cleaned our room once! If we wanted the room cleaned daily, it is a $50 charge per day. This is ridiculous! They only give 2 towels per room and 2 tiny square pillows. We had to ask the staff for more pillows. Who wants to sleep on a tiny travel pillow for a week?! Along with this, no one refills coffee/tea in room. No one changes the towels, no one empties the TINY garbage bin (only one garbage bin in the room). We had to go out to the market to buy our own coffee & tea.

- Hotel Breakfast is $15 per person per day. Nothing special! Cheaper and mode fresh to go to a cafe a couple minute walk away.

- NO free coffee or drinks in lobby.

- If you do not clean up your own dishes in the rooms, they will charge you $50.

- You have to throw your own trash away. Front desk said room cleaning service does not do this and they will charge. They told us it’s on the first floor, which we never found.

- If you want to use the pool/sauna it is $25 a day, or $10 an hour! Ridiculous! We never saw anyone use it.

- When booking, do not choose a room on the first floor (same floor as front desk). There are no views on first floor.

- No AC or fans in the room. We were there in Sept and the cold wind was perfect and we just left the window open during the day and it was cool inside the room.

We will never stay here again. The service we received was ridiculous. We do not recommend it at all. Beware, nothing here is free and they charge for everything.

There are many other great hotels around. We will not be back at this hotel.

My college age daughter and I spent a week here. It was booked about 2 months in advance, I took great care in my selection for lodging. We loved the neighborhood, although the winding cobblestone streets did fool us a bit. The building is updated, very clean and tidy. Our room was small, but had all the essentials. Enjoyed the small kitchenette, definitely enjoyed prepping a few simple meals there and we're pleased with the provisions in terms of dishes, pots and pans, great coffee maker and hot water pot. Little fridge with small freezer and a miniature dishwasher. Our bathroom was small but very nice, large soaking tub, lively fixtures, I encourage you to bring a candle or two and some bathbombs, and enjoy a true zen experience, really a great tub. Bed was comfy, our window was large and sent lovely breezes through the room all night. Now for the criticisms: the personnel were generally friendly but not exactly warm if you know what I mean. It was not an expectation for me that the room would get daily maid service, however since she is there making up other rooms, why not leave us some fresh towels about Midway through the week? I had to ask for the following: toilet paper, fresh towels, and where to dispose of my (full) garbage mid week. Instead of having someone pick it up, they sent me to the basement where I wondered aimlessly until finding a creepy area with dumpsters. Seriously that was weird. Bring that they call themselves "apart'hotel", hotel is a word I combine with some level of hospitality, come on and do that please. Do NOT make me wonder looking for dumpsters. It's not an air bnb ya know. I would really have appreciated a courtesy stop for towels, toilet paper, and garbage pick up. In addition to that, how about a roll of paper towels, a coffee filter or 2, and some dishwashing product for the dishwasher. It would he so nice. You can do better.

The hotel was ideal and very well situated. The room was well equipped and very comfortable. The only negative for the stay was the quoted price of €25 pppd for the spa. We would not spend a whole day in the spa, an hourly rate would have been a better option.It’s location at the top of montmartre was an ideal base for our break as long as you can come with the walk up.

It’s all been renovated and like others have said great location, friendly staff, lovely and clean, ok breakfast if you don’t have the energy to go out... what’s the catch?? In the summer you need AC and there is none. This makes an enormous difference to comfort during a stay.

It’s available in the foyer but as soon as you hit your bedroom it so hot and stuffy. We were there when temps hit 35 degrees and with no through draft sat cooking at night.

I liken it to building a really smart new car but forgetting to but any padding on the seat frames. Admittedly you don’t need it to have a ride but it would sure make the ride a lot nicer.

I knew all about the AC before booking and so this is not a complaint - merely an observation that would definitely make me think twice about booking there again in the warmer months.

Any other time the temp doesn’t nudge over 20 - 25 degrees it would be my number one choice.

Room tips: ask for a room overlooking the courtyard but not on the first floor. If it’s on the first floor, one or two of the rooms are accessible directly from the garden - a bit disconcerting when you’re forced to have the window open all night to know anyone could access your room. To get a view like the picture I have posted it will need to be the first few rooms closest to the lift/stairs. The noise isn’t an issue but you’ll get a nice outlook.

We arrived at our hotel not knowing the hotel was on top of a hill *please note that being fit is a bonus as there is alot of stairs in pairs especially near here* we used the metro to get to the hotel as the nearest station was Anvers which was perfect as there was a stair lift to go up and down part of the hill which we could use with our five day metro ticket (would recommend around 65 euros each but we definitely got our money's worth rather than using taxis etc) the hotel was lovely a/c at reception spoke English which was helpful as our french isn't great. The gentleman was really helpful as we asked if we could check in slightly earlier and he checked if our room was ready which it was to our delight. Rooms are very modern and lovely looking there is hair and body wash and hand soap and washing up liquid provided. However we took our own hair and body wash so we didn't use. The kitchen facilities were great a hob, microwave, dishwasher, fridge and freezer (small freezer). We used this most days par one and it was lovely however there isn't an extractor fan so be careful when cooking any meat in the frying pan (we set of the alarm but they came to check on us before emptying the building via knocking on the door and a phone call. There is a safe in the room which is handy and don't have to pay extra for. Our rooms were cleaned and bins empties etc if we put the sign on the door asking them to clean it. However they did take our towels and not replace with clean ones so we went to reception who were apologetic and said they were still being cleaned and they will bring some up asap. Which they did. The only disadvantage as stated in other reviews is no air con, me and my partner really struggled to sleep because of the heat (34) and it was incredibly draining. The mattress was too hard for me as well so had to sleep on the duvet but got to hot on the duvet and pillows were too soft so had to sleep with no pillows. Maybe a selection of different types of pillows would be good. Because of no a/c or fans (we didn't ask they might have had some in reception) but we used damp towels to cool us down. Our room had shutters which was nice to get some privacy at night and leave it slightly open at the bottom for air. Our toliet decided not to flush for about 6 hours which was weird told reception and they said someone will come look at some point soon as he doesn't know how the system works and it just randomly started working halfway through the night which was weird. I would give this place 4* it's only due to a few bits it's not a five I hope this review helps others decide 😊

We happened to arrive in Paris during a heat wave. The lobby is air conditioned, but that is it. The hallways are stifling. The rooms - even with the windows open (which meant no privacy because the only way to open the windows was to open the curtains) were unbearably hot. We even asked at the front because the bathroom mirror had a sticker on it saying - save energy with a list - and on the list it said turn off the air conditioner. Not to mention, it was so hot the bathroom smelled of mold and when you opened the hotel door it took a while to get used to the smell. The front desk explained that they opened in December - that was the only reason we were given why there was no air conditioning. In addition, to use the spa/exercise room - it is 25 Euros per person per day. (though website said 20 Euro). 100Euros per day for our family of 4 was not something we would do. . Great location though - and it did force us to stay out and power through from sun up to after sun down - just to be outside or at another location to stay out of the heat. It is a bummer because it was truly a great location and nice room layout.

The place itself is in an excellent location. Right behind the Sacre Coeur and in the heart of Montmartre. It is new and rooms are modern with all required facilities. I visited in July when the weather was absolutely gorgeous. On arrival we were greeted by a lovely receptionist who was always helpful and smiling so we were excited for our stay.

On arrival to our room the heat was stifling as we stepped through the door and we immediately opened a window in the hope that would help... during our 3 night stay the temperature in the room was unbearable and it put a real dampener on our stay and I would go as far to say it ruined it. We were unable to relax and sleep at night due to the excessive heat in the room. I simply can’t understand how a hotel in this day and age which is new has no air conditioning. We had the windows open non stop throughout our stay in the hope of some rest bite or a bit of wind which never came.... don’t think we should have had to rely on this to have a comfortable stay. As we had window open this meant we were unable to close the curtains therefore light was beaming in early morning and directly opposite the Apartments there is a children’s nursery so from early morning there is constant screaming and noise from the playing children which is very loud. I reported the immense heat in the room to evening staff on reception who couldn’t have cared less... his reply ‘I know’!!! The conditions are simply inhuman and people are paying for this! Avoid like the plague when weather is good! Disappointing as Apartments are nice and in great location.

We stayed at this hotel upon our return to Paris for our flight the next morning, The staff were very friendly and hospitable. The room was very nice and updated. We did not have a use for the kitchenette but it was a nice feature. They missed a few things and that’s why I gave them a 4 instead of 5. First, none of the bathroom soap dispenser pumps worked so I had to yank our the container to have shampoo, body wash/soap. Second, instant coffee?! Really?! Nesspresso or something similar is really the new standard in all hotels inside your room in EU. They did have a nessoresso machine downstairs that you had to pay to buy and that did not really sit well with me. I told the hotel staff and they chuckled in agreement.

Fantastic place almost on the very top of Montmartre, in a very quiet street yet conveniently close both to Sacré-Coeur and to busy streets with nice restaurants and shops. Large rooms with basich kitchen facilities; if you are lucky, your windows will open into a quiet garden, and in the evening you may hear accordeon music seeping in... Good basic service, helpful staff.
Lack of air conditioning is somewhat unpleasant on hot days. And the great location means that for almost every return from the city, you will have to walk up a steep hill, usually including stairs, so physical fitness is a must here.

This was a difficult review to write, whilst some stuff was very good it was let down by penny pinching attitude. We had a one bedroom apartment and it was a very good size. Modern and clean. The biggest disappointment though was no A/C. The reception area and breakfast area have A/C but not the rooms! Why do that? This is a brand new hotel. People want and expect A/C nowadays. We had a ground floor room and had to have the windows open all the time as it was stifling in the room otherwise. Consequently it was really noisy and difficult to sleep. Other annoying things. Room is not cleaned at all while you are here (we stayed 5 nights). Nor are the towels changed. You have at ask at reception for more sachets of coffee which they don’t want to give out as those left are “a gift”. Come off it. It’s a sachet of coffee for Christ sakes. And you have to ask for additional toilet rolls. Those were given out without a problem. We had one breakfast here. Not terrible but not worth the money. Lots of nearby cafes, restaurants and local boulangerie that are much better value. The kitchenette in the room was good with plenty of equipment. We made our own breakfasts after the first day. Good location in Paris. All in all not bad but not as good as I was hoping for. I’d come again but NOT in the summer.

Stayed here for business, but would be perfectly happy to return for leisure. The hotel is modern, clean, and spacious. While it does not offer full hotel services, rooms do benefit from aparthotel features such as mini-kitchen. Location is a highlight - a 200m walk to the buzz of Montmartre, but so quiet you wouldn't know it. The area to the immediate north (down the hill) is well worth exploring for restaurants, bars, shops. No aircon, but absolutely not necessary either. Wifi good and free. Breakfast looked average, but remember it's an aparthotel....so you should be either making your own or eating out! Overall, good value (for Paris). I would definitely return.

The appart hotel has good points:
Good Cleaning
Good Size of the room
Excellent Living Room
24h Lugagge Store
Early check in - if there are available room

But the bad points disturb out stay:
No air conditioning- ok we could open the window but the room becomes noisy and light

There’s no bottle opener in the entire place - even classified as apart hotel

Anyway it was a good choice

A fantastic hotel! It's beautiful, spacious and modern. The rooms, especially for Paris, are huge, and very very comfortable. Could have stayed here for a week, rather than just the two nights. Reasonably priced, great location. Our window had a partial view of the Sacre Coeur, and with the windows open we got to enjoy the church bells - but only at reasonable times! The rest of the time, it was very quiet. It is slightly difficult to access from the Metro if you have lots of luggage, as the nearest metro station has almost 100 stairs to get up out of it, and then it's an uphill walk from there. Also the rooms don't have AC, which was okay while we were there in early June, before it got too hot, but would probably be a struggle when it's warmer. The windows do open, and we slept with them open, but if you're worried about mosquitos in summer, be aware of this. The staff were also not very helpful when we asked them anything, but weren't bad either - just did what they needed to do. The room also had a fridge, tiny dishwasher, and all the required amenities in the little kitchenette. If we were staying for longer, we would definitely have used it! And we would definitely love to stay again!

Very impressed with the aparthotel, as long as you are not expecting a hotel service then you will not be disappointed. There is a reception and breakfast is available but why would you eat here when you are in Paris! Loads of great places to eat breakfast nearby. You do need to be happy to walk a lot to stay here as all he shops/bars and restaurants are a short but steep walk but Mont means hill do you should be prepared!
Yes there is no air con but as we are in Northern Europe I would not expect it. Our window opened fully is you messed about with the curtains a bit and we slept well with a nice cool breeze.
I would definitely stay here again.

Stayed for three nights on business.
The room was comfortable with good wi-fi but I was kept waiting for ten minutes to check in while the two staff prepared a customer’s photocopying.
Breakfast was okay if minimal. First of all you need to find one of the seven tables that has actually been cleared. The coffee machine dispensed hot chocolate on the cappuccino button - and continued to do so on the third day even after it was pointed out.
This was better than the juice machine which was empty.
Be frugal with the meagre in room coffee sachets. These are a ‘welcome gift’ according to reception and not replenished however many nights you stay - and the previous day’s dirty cups remain dirty.
It’s a shame for this new (two taxi drivers couldn’t find it) hotel because it has a lot of potential.
I don’t think I will be back.

We booked this hotel for our five day stay. We were told we could open the window for a breeze as there was no air conditioning. When we realized the window was locked, we were told it could not be opened due to it being a historic building. Nice room but right off a loud street. If sweating is your thing, book here. We couldn’t cancel our room since we booked through trip advisor so we were out $500 and had to pay an additional $400 for a new hotel. Our comfort was worth it but a terrible experience all around.

Everything was all right.I think our next stay in Paris will be here.This is a very comfortable hote.The place is very peaceful and close to all attractions of Montmartre, it is also close to the metro station and good bars and restaurants.

Clean, tidy, modern hotel in a great location. The rooms are a good size & very clean, the only downside is that they are not air conditioned, so do get very warm during humid weather. The windows do open fully, so if there is a breeze, you can get some air circulating. Friendly, accommodating staff, would definitely recommend.

Pros: location, window view, size of the room, everything brand new
Cons: no AC. Actually there is an AC but they do not turn it on. It is a central AC. It is a building and you can’t even sleep without an air. Short staff. The check-in is a killer. The management of the hotel seems to be cheap, so not enough people working there to clean rooms. I came there at noon. They told me that room is not ready and check-in at 3:00pm. Fine, but I got my room at 4:00 pm and it smelled all detergent and no AC, and only one side of the window is possible to open. Also small details are missing like some oil, salt and pepper in the room. It seems like this hotel was meant to be one night stand, so why to bother with kitchen then.
Over all,it was ok: clean and new, but next time I will go somewhere else.

These apartments were perfect! My boyfriend booked them as a surprise and they were great. The location right in front of the sacre-coeur however there was no noise from the busy crowds. They were cleaned every day and fresh towels. The kitchen had everything you could need- fridge, dishwasher, coffee machine, microwave etc. Metros close by also so travel round Paris. Check out is 12 but reception also hold your luggage which is convenient. Overall, a perfect stay!

Thanks for making our engagement weekend in Paris a blast. The 4th floor apartment was a royal treat with the panoramic view.
On the constructive feedback side the rooms are going to get very hot in the summer, there is limited airflow in the rooms and one is unable to fully open the windows (as the curtains hooks run flash to the window). Hopefully Odalys will make standing fans available to guests.
As we stayed 4 nights we had the hotel cleaning service which was fab. However it felt mean to run out of toilet paper, to have no milk sachets and that the tea/coffee wasn't refilled once used on the first day. Be aware that this is first and foremost serviced apartments, so studios are not serviced daily if you stay more than 4 days. So don't expect it.
Still had a great stay, the quiet area, the cafes of Montmartre and amazing view at night made our exploration of Paris purrfect.
Will definitely stay there again.

The rooms are very clean and spacious. We were there for a weekend of sightseeing so the location is perfect in my favourite spot of Paris. The customer service is very low, apart from the receptionist who checked us in whose communication in English was quite bad but he was attentive. SPA access has an extra cost however nobody informs you about that. After a day of walking we decided to go to relax to the SPA and we asked to the Italian receptionist who quite moody started to type in his computer and after a while he asked us how would you like to pay. We were quite in shock but decided not to go and he came across quite rude. He will recommend you an Italian restaurant in moulin rouge because he obviously has commission from every table booked. Next day upon check out he attended us again and was begging for a tripadvisor review and after telling him I work in hospitality his attitude changed to try to be extremely friendly.
Great hotel to rest and for us was perfect but don’t expect anything from the staff.

Excellent location, walk to the top of Sacre Couer, and yet on a very quiet street. Excellent restaurants and coffee houses nearby. Metro is very close. Good people, polite and helpful. Helpful staff, very clean

This hotel is brand new, there is NO CARPET in the rooms (finally!), the rooms are large (and I mean US-Large, which is quite impossible to find in Paris), the service was excellent and the location is perfect. The beds are very comfortable and, again, large. They have REAL king-size beds, not two bed that they put together. One thing: there is no sheet between the duvet and the mattress cover, like the North-Americans are used to. But I can assure you that the duvet was changed and was very clean. Also (I didn't ask for, my bad) I think that there is no face towel (again, a North American thing). Please note that you are in Montmartre, which means that the streets are very trick and there is lot (and I mean a lot) of stairs even if it's called a street! The breakfast is complete (with eggs, meat and everything else you'll find in a French hotel). There is a spa downstairs (hot tub and hammam I believe) but you have to pay an extra fee for this. I didn't try yet, and I say yet because I will definitely return to this hotel for my upcoming stays in Paris.

Beautifully located in the vicinity of the Sacre Couer , close to the restaurants and a ten minute walk from the closest metro station... this modern styled hotel was perfect... we spent four nights there and we had one problem with the room temperature... but upon speaking to reception they quickly changed our room without any hesitation ... All the staff where really helpful and would recommend this hotel to anyone thinking of staying in Paris...

We went to Paris for a rugby international and stayed at the Odalys. The location is excellent right beside The Sacre Couer and the main Montmartre area. The room was spacious and spotlessly clean. The receptionist, Fabio, was very friendly and a treasure of knowledge on the area. Great views across the city. We look forward to returning in two years time!

Stayed for one night as a group of friends. The location was excellent, just at the back of the Sacre Cour and all that Montmatre has to offer was within walking distance. As with most of Montmatre its on a hill and we had to trek up a long set of stairs to get from the metro. The staff were friendly and the rooms were clean and had everything we needed.

We enjoyed our 4 day stay here. The room is spotless and the king sized bed was so comfortable. The staff were cordial, especially Fabio put extra effort into making sure we had an enjoyable stay and also assisted us by suggesting we use the hotel shuttle to return to the airport. The hotel is delightful, modern and new and very quiet. We loved the location, just a few minutes walk to the metro and to many shopping streets. We would love to return.

WE went for a weekend to Paris, and stayed at the Odalys City hotel in París. We had a great time. Firstly, the staff at the hotel is just great. It really makes a difference in the service.
In addition, the location is very good. The premises are very nice and the view in the rooms is just awesome.
I would definitely stay again.

The hotel cancelled my reservation just hours before arrival because they apparently couldn't process my American express card. I was then forced to rebook the same room at a much higher rate. Staff refused to help. Overall a very disappointing experience.

Apart from the above the hotel is in a great location and is brand new. Downside was that our room still smelled of fresh paint.

The location was excellent, close to Sacre Coeur and amazing restaurants and cafes. Our room was great and had a stunning view across Paris from the 4’th floor so that it felt like we were up at Sacre Coeur. The hotel staff was very friendly and helpful and recommended us some great activities to do in Paris.
Excellent value for money!

The best value for money you can get in Paris. The hotel is right next to Sacre Coeur, and in Montmarte hence very easily accessible to infinite choices of cafes, bistros and bars. The view from the room is over Paris and absolutelt gorgeous. The Hotel staff has been very kind and accomodating especially Fabio who has provided us excellent tips for places to visit around Paris and has been very helpful. I would say without hesitation that I would return here next time I am in Paris.
